I am the President of Kaysim Housing Group, Inc.  a state licensed personal care home that I have operated for 21 years.  My staff deserves a living wage and paid vacation. Due to systemic racism and governmental redlining, our residents who are diagnosed with a severe persistent mental illness and are SSI recipients (whom my staff and I consider extended family) are only able to pay $37 per day, per person for the 24 hr. staff supervised care we provide.
We save lives and Medicaid dollars yet non of these savings are returned to us, but instead are used to fund every other mental health housing model.  WHY?
